<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFBrook.2C_G.L._and_R.F._Leslie_.28eds..291963.E2.80.931978">Brook, G.L. and R.F. Leslie (eds.) (1963–1978). <i><a href="http://etext.lib.virginia.edu/etcbin/toccer-new2?id=LayBruO.sgm&amp;images=images/modeng&amp;data=/lv1/Archive/mideng-parsed&amp;tag=public&amp;part=all" class="external text" title="http://etext.lib.virginia.edu/etcbin/toccer-new2?id=LayBruO.sgm&amp;images=images/modeng&amp;data=/lv1/Archive/mideng-parsed&amp;tag=public&amp;part=all" rel="nofollow">British Museum Ms. Cotton Caligula A. IX and British Museum Ms. Cotton Otho C. XIII</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Early_English_Text_Society" title="Early English Text Society">Early English Text Society</a>. Oxford University Press. pp.&#160;287<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://etext.lib.virginia.edu/etcbin/toccer-new2?id=LayBruO.sgm&amp;images=images/modeng&amp;data=/lv1/Archive/mideng-parsed&amp;tag=public&amp;part=all" class="external free" title="http://etext.lib.virginia.edu/etcbin/toccer-new2?id=LayBruO.sgm&amp;images=images/modeng&amp;data=/lv1/Archive/mideng-parsed&amp;tag=public&amp;part=all" rel="nofollow">http://etext.lib.virginia.edu/etcbin/toccer-new2?id=LayBruO.sgm&amp;images=images/modeng&amp;data=/lv1/Archive/mideng-parsed&amp;tag=public&amp;part=all</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2006-10-30</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=British+Museum+Ms.+Cotton+Caligula+A.+IX+and+British+Museum+Ms.+Cotton+Otho+C.+XIII&amp;rft.aulast=Brook%2C+G.L.+and+R.F.+Leslie+%28eds.%29&amp;rft.au=Brook%2C+G.L.+and+R.F.+Leslie+%28eds.%29&amp;rft.date=1963%E2%80%931978&amp;rft.series=%5B%5BEarly+English+Text+Society%5D%5D&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B287&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fetext.lib.virginia.edu%2Fetcbin%2Ftoccer-new2%3Fid%3DLayBruO.sgm%26images%3Dimages%2Fmodeng%26data%3D%2Flv1%2FArchive%2Fmideng-parsed%26tag%3Dpublic%26part%3Dall&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Split_infinitive"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Nagle-4">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Nagle_4-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nagle_4-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nagle_4-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nagle_4-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> Nagle (1994). Nagle takes his historical data from <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFVisser1997">Visser, F. T. (1997) [1973]. <i>An Historical Syntax of the English Language</i>. Leiden: Brill. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9004032738" class="internal">ISBN 90-04-03273-8</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=An+Historical+Syntax+of+the+English+Language&amp;rft.aulast=Visser&amp;rft.aufirst=F.+T.&amp;rft.au=Visser%2C+F.+T.&amp;rft.date=1997&amp;rft.place=Leiden&amp;rft.pub=Brill&amp;rft.isbn=90-04-03273-8&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Split_infinitive"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5" title="">^</a></b> Quoted by <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFHall1882">Hall, Fitzedward (1882). "On the Separation, by a Word or Words, of to and the Infinitive Mood". <i>American Journal of Philology</i> <b>3</b> (9): 17–24. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.2307%2F287307" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.2307%2F287307" rel="nofollow">10.2307/287307</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=On+the+Separation%2C+by+a+Word+or+Words%2C+of+to+and+the+Infinitive+Mood&amp;rft.jtitle=American+Journal+of+Philology&amp;rft.aulast=Hall&amp;rft.aufirst=Fitzedward&amp;rft.au=Hall%2C+Fitzedward&amp;rft.date=1882&amp;rft.volume=3&amp;rft.issue=9&amp;rft.pages=17%E2%80%9324&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.2307%2F287307&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Split_infinitive"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>; <a href="/wiki/William_Strunk_Jr." title="William Strunk Jr." class="mw-redirect">Strunk, William</a> &amp; <a href="/wiki/E._B._White" title="E. B. White">White, E.B.</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/The_Elements_of_Style" title="The Elements of Style">The Elements of Style</a></i>, fourth edition, Longman, 2000, p. 58, also speak of 14th-century examples.</li>
<li id="cite_note-AHBEU-6">^ <a href="#cite_ref-AHBEU_6-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-AHBEU_6-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-AHBEU_6-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="http://www.bartleby.com/64/C001/059.html" class="external text" title="http://www.bartleby.com/64/C001/059.html" rel="nofollow"><i>The American Heritage Book of English Usage</i> on split infinitives</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-Hall-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Hall_7-0" title="">^</a></b> Hall (1882)</li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFCurme1927">Curme, George (May 1927). "The Split Infinitive". <i>American Speech</i> <b>2</b> (8): 341–342. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.2307%2F452976" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.2307%2F452976" rel="nofollow">10.2307/452976</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=The+Split+Infinitive&amp;rft.jtitle=American+Speech&amp;rft.aulast=Curme&amp;rft.aufirst=George&amp;rft.au=Curme%2C+George&amp;rft.date=May+1927&amp;rft.volume=2&amp;rft.issue=8&amp;rft.pages=341%E2%80%93342&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.2307%2F452976&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Split_infinitive"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
