<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFNagle1994">Nagle, Stephen (1994). <a href="http://books.google.com/books?visbn=3110141272&amp;id=25yCVi0AA4cC&amp;pg=PA234&amp;lpg=PA234&amp;dq=Nagle+split+infinitive+infl&amp;sig=ypsKtqSBrmSELIGok3xuLVjEN6w" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?visbn=3110141272&amp;id=25yCVi0AA4cC&amp;pg=PA234&amp;lpg=PA234&amp;dq=Nagle+split+infinitive+infl&amp;sig=ypsKtqSBrmSELIGok3xuLVjEN6w" rel="nofollow">"Infl in Early Modern English and the status of <i>to</i>"</a>. in Dieter Kastovsky (Ed.). <i>Studies in Early Modern English</i>. Berlin; New York: Mouton de Gruyter. pp.&#160;233–242. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/3110141272" class="internal">ISBN 3-11-014127-2</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?visbn=3110141272&amp;id=25yCVi0AA4cC&amp;pg=PA234&amp;lpg=PA234&amp;dq=Nagle+split+infinitive+infl&amp;sig=ypsKtqSBrmSELIGok3xuLVjEN6w" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?visbn=3110141272&amp;id=25yCVi0AA4cC&amp;pg=PA234&amp;lpg=PA234&amp;dq=Nagle+split+infinitive+infl&amp;sig=ypsKtqSBrmSELIGok3xuLVjEN6w" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?visbn=3110141272&amp;id=25yCVi0AA4cC&amp;pg=PA234&amp;lpg=PA234&amp;dq=Nagle+split+infinitive+infl&amp;sig=ypsKtqSBrmSELIGok3xuLVjEN6w</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2006-10-27</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Infl++in+Early+Modern+English+and+the+status+of+%27%27to%27%27&amp;rft.atitle=Studies+in+Early+Modern+English&amp;rft.aulast=Nagle&amp;rft.aufirst=Stephen&amp;rft.au=Nagle%2C+Stephen&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B233%E2%80%93242&amp;rft.place=Berlin%3B+New+York&amp;rft.pub=Mouton+de+Gruyter&amp;rft.isbn=3-11-014127-2&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fvisbn%3D3110141272%26id%3D25yCVi0AA4cC%26pg%3DPA234%26lpg%3DPA234%